README for .../gallery/2dprob/problem.04/figures/fig4

As of 3/26: animations have been moved to:  .../gallery/2dprob/problem.04/animations/fig4

The .mp4 files were generated by ANIM8Z10 from the movie tarballs produced by ZEUS during the runs (e.g., ziwnkq.01.tar.gz).  The .s and .mac files for the delv=1.0 run is in .../gallery/test2d/problem.03, where "delv" (and possibly "courno") is the only namelist parameter to be changed for the other runs.  The input file inanim8z used is:

 $animcon  mpgfmt=4, frate=24, infmt=3, kpppm=1
         , infile='ziwnkq.01.tar.gz','zid_kq.01.tar.gz'
         , iflip =1,1
         , colmm =0,2
         , colmin=-19.1,0.0
         , colmax=0.16,0.0
         , nlog  =-10,0
         , pal   =2,2                                           $

Extrema for the density animations (in subdirectory density/ and which have not been incorporated into the web page) were calculated as global extrema by ANIM8Z10.  The minima for the vorticity animations were set to be 75% of the actual minimum, and the maxima were determined individually for each run (remained at 0.2 once 2M > 1).

Vorticity extrema used for the .mp4 files in this directory are as follows:

	   actual	used in .mp4
2M=	min	max	min	max
--------------------------------------
0.25	-6.25	 0.026	 -4.69	0.05
0.50	-12.5	 0.028	 -9.38	0.09
0.75	-18.9	 0.023	-14.1	0.12
1.00	-25.4	 0.021	-19.1	0.16
1.25	-32.3	 1.10	-24.0	0.20
1.50	-39.4	14.3	-29.6	0.20
1.75	-46.8	27.8	-35.1	0.20
2.00	-57.7	37.4	-43.3	0.20
2.25	-63.5	46.3	-47.6	0.20
2.50	-70.6	55.0	-53.0	0.20
2.75	-79.3	11.4	-59.5	0.20
3.00	-83.4	 0.067	-62.6	0.20


The thumbnails were created from the last .ppm file for each animation.  As usual, convert produces unnecessarily large .ps files when converting directly from anything.  Thus, to get files 60-70% the size:

convert 2m=0.25_wn.ppm 2m=0.25_wn.jpg

then open up the .jpg file in preview (don't forget to turn the "auto-rotate" off), and save it from there in postscript.

Logan's convert command for cropping an image at the same time:

convert -crop 250x250+125 +repage d_cn0.50.ppm test.eps


